I""<p>Even if <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/stress-induced-disease-is-a-metabolic-prioritization-issue">prolonged periods of intense stress causes disease</a>, a complete lack of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-seeks-homeostasis">stressors</a> is extremely boring. In light doses, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-seeks-homeostasis">stress</a> is useful and pleasant, such as when <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/contrasting-difficulties-are-like-price-decoys">tackling challenges</a>.</p>
